The warrior epic analogy really doesn't work, the difference being the warrior makes the choice not to use the epic (for whatever reason, but he still makes the choice), while the game engine makes the choice for the druid.  The trend for a while now, with each expansion is to take more and more tools away from the druid and pass some others out to other classes.<br>
<br>
You can either buy or exp to get permanent sow.  Many mobs are unsarable, unrootable.  Druids ability to port has had additional roadblocks in every expansion.  Originally many mobs were tuned for lures, hurting both druids and mages.  Ultimately, that isn't the point of the petition, but just part of the druid experience.<br>
<br>
Noone would expect a warrior to tank a high level Luclin mob with Kurnark equipment.  Ultimately, that is what is being asked of druids in the role of secondary healers on raids.  <br>
<br>
Every mob is tuned with two damage numbers in mind.  Target specific damage over time (generally and hopefully for the raid the MT) and AE damage over time.  Combat is ultimately just a mathmatical equation.  What high level raiding druids (and guilds) are finding is that during time T (the time to kill a mob) given their mana pool M (including mana regen from all sources) they cannot keep up with the secondary damage over time with the current tools they have available. (Also a limiting factor is number of participants on a raid. . . too many cause too much lag for everyone and can lead to failure)  Verant obviously has the exact mathmatics for each mob and if the math on any of the suggestions proves to be off, they can adjust it.  <br>
<br>
Not all druids want to be healers, but since that is the role we are generally relegated to during raids, that is what the petition focused on.  New spells or role ideas would be great, but other than disagreeing with the solution, most dissenters offer no solutions.  (Nor were they around during the many weeks this petition was debated)  <br>
